{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1072,"text":"Today's computers are so amazing"},{"time":4810,"text":"that we fail to notice\nhow terrible they really are."},{"time":10172,"text":"I'd like to talk to you today\nabout this problem,"},{"time":12594,"text":"and how we can fix it with neuroscience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16056,"text":"First, I'd like to take you back\nto a frosty night in Harlem in 2011"},{"time":20097,"text":"that had a profound impact on me."},{"time":22437,"text":"I was sitting in a dive bar\noutside of Columbia University,"},{"time":25635,"text":"where I studied computer science\nand neuroscience,"},{"time":28567,"text":"and I was having this great conversation\nwith a fellow student"},{"time":31659,"text":"about the power of holograms\nto one day replace computers."},{"time":35390,"text":"And just as we were getting\nto the best part of the conversation,"},{"time":38503,"text":"of course, his phone lights up."},{"time":40621,"text":"And he pulls it towards himself,\nand he looks down and he starts typing."},{"time":45070,"text":"And then he forces his eyeballs\nback up to mine and he goes,"},{"time":48277,"text":"\"Keep going. I'm with you.\""},{"time":50404,"text":"But of course his eyes were glazed over,"},{"time":52785,"text":"and the moment was dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54964,"text":"Meanwhile across the bar,"},{"time":56208,"text":"I noticed another student\nholding his phone,"},{"time":58516,"text":"this time towards a group."},{"time":59985,"text":"He was swiping through\npictures on Instagram,"},{"time":62769,"text":"and these kids were laughing hysterically."},{"time":65327,"text":"And that dichotomy\nbetween how crappy I was feeling"},{"time":68870,"text":"and how happy they were feeling\nabout the same technology,"},{"time":71672,"text":"really got me thinking."},{"time":73074,"text":"And the more I thought of it,\nthe more I realized"},{"time":75431,"text":"it was clearly not the digital information\nthat was the bad guy here,"},{"time":79227,"text":"it was simply the display position\nthat was separating me from my friend"},{"time":82958,"text":"and that was binding those kids together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85608,"text":"See, they were connected around something,"},{"time":87831,"text":"just like our ancestors\nwho evolved their social cognitions"},{"time":91253,"text":"telling stories around the campfire."},{"time":93857,"text":"And that's exactly what tools\nshould do, I think."},{"time":96225,"text":"They should extend our bodies."},{"time":97728,"text":"And I think computers today\nare doing quite the opposite."},{"time":100939,"text":"Whether you're sending\nan email to your wife"},{"time":103191,"text":"or you're composing a symphony"},{"time":105237,"text":"or just consoling a friend,"},{"time":106865,"text":"you're doing it in pretty\nmuch the same way."},{"time":109235,"text":"You're hunched over these rectangles,"},{"time":111492,"text":"fumbling with buttons and menus\nand more rectangles."},{"time":114759,"text":"And I think this is the wrong way,"},{"time":116780,"text":"I think we can start using\na much more natural machine."},{"time":120232,"text":"We should use machines that bring\nour work back into the world."},{"time":123774,"text":"We should use machines that use\nthe principles of neuroscience"},{"time":126817,"text":"to extend our senses\nversus going against them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131305,"text":"Now it just so happens\nthat I have such a machine here."},{"time":134116,"text":"It's called the Meta 2."},{"time":135297,"text":"Let's try it out."},{"time":145617,"text":"Now in front of me right now,\nI can see the audience,"},{"time":148454,"text":"and I can see my very hands."},{"time":151026,"text":"And in three, two, one,"},{"time":153227,"text":"we're going to see an immersive\nhologram appear,"},{"time":156003,"text":"a very realistic hologram\nappear in front of me,"},{"time":158307,"text":"of our very glasses I'm wearing\non my head right now."},{"time":160895,"text":"And of course this could be\nanything that we're shopping for"},{"time":163760,"text":"or learning from,"},{"time":164935,"text":"and I can use my hands"},{"time":166302,"text":"to very nicely kind of move\nit around with fine control."},{"time":170434,"text":"And I think Iron Man would be proud."},{"time":174643,"text":"We're going to come back\nto this in just a bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177783,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179971,"text":"Now if you're anything like me,\nyour mind is already reeling"},{"time":182906,"text":"with the possibilities of what we can do\nwith this kind of technology,"},{"time":186231,"text":"so let's look at a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187413,"text":"My mom is an architect,"},{"time":188587,"text":"so naturally the first thing I imagined"},{"time":190516,"text":"was laying out a building in 3D space"},{"time":193021,"text":"instead of having to use\nthese 2D floor plans."},{"time":195437,"text":"She's actually touching graphics right now"},{"time":197926,"text":"and selecting an interior decor."},{"time":199727,"text":"This was all shot through a GoPro\nthrough our very glasses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203115,"text":"And this next use case\nis very personal to me,"},{"time":205754,"text":"it's Professor Adam Gazzaley's\nglass brain project,"},{"time":209192,"text":"courtesy of UCSF."},{"time":211107,"text":"As a neuroscience student,"},{"time":212826,"text":"I would always fantasize"},{"time":214247,"text":"about the ability to learn and memorize\nthese complex brain structures"},{"time":219710,"text":"with an actual machine,"},{"time":220901,"text":"where I could touch and play\nwith the various brain structures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224535,"text":"Now what you're seeing\nis called augmented reality,"},{"time":228085,"text":"but to me, it's part\nof a much more important story --"},{"time":231512,"text":"a story of how we can begin\nto extend our bodies with digital devices,"},{"time":238227,"text":"instead of the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241734,"text":"Now ..."},{"time":243227,"text":"in the next few years, humanity's\ngoing to go through a shift, I think."},{"time":246613,"text":"We're going to start putting\nan entire layer of digital information"},{"time":249850,"text":"on the real world."},{"time":252050,"text":"Just imagine for a moment"},{"time":253342,"text":"what this could mean for storytellers,"},{"time":255626,"text":"for painters,"},{"time":256965,"text":"for brain surgeons,"},{"time":259147,"text":"for interior decorators"},{"time":260988,"text":"and maybe for all of us here today."},{"time":263544,"text":"And what I think we need\nto do as a community,"},{"time":265735,"text":"is really try and make an effort"},{"time":267751,"text":"to imagine how we can\ncreate this new reality"},{"time":270666,"text":"in a way that extends\nthe human experience,"},{"time":273388,"text":"instead of gamifying our reality"},{"time":275380,"text":"or cluttering it with digital information."},{"time":277467,"text":"And that's what I'm very passionate about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280318,"text":"Now, I want to tell you a little secret."},{"time":282503,"text":"In about five years --"},{"time":283694,"text":"this is not the smallest device --"},{"time":285344,"text":"in about five years,"},{"time":286536,"text":"these are all going to look like\nstrips of glass on our eyes"},{"time":289488,"text":"that project holograms."},{"time":291426,"text":"And just like we don't care so much\nabout which phone we buy"},{"time":294760,"text":"in terms of the hardware -- we buy it\nfor the operating system --"},{"time":298205,"text":"as a neuroscientist,"},{"time":299388,"text":"I always dreamt of building\nthe iOS of the mind, if you will."},{"time":304537,"text":"And it's very, very important\nthat we get this right,"},{"time":307441,"text":"because we might be living\ninside of these things"},{"time":309759,"text":"for at least as long as we've lived"},{"time":311471,"text":"with the Windows graphical user interface."},{"time":314136,"text":"And I don't know about you,"},{"time":315477,"text":"but living inside of Windows scares me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318009,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319353,"text":"To isolate the single most intuitive\ninterface out of infinity,"},{"time":323267,"text":"we use neuroscience to drive\nour design guidelines,"},{"time":325971,"text":"instead of letting a bunch of designers\nfight it out in the boardroom."},{"time":329585,"text":"And the principle we all revolve around"},{"time":332258,"text":"is what's called the \"Neural Path\nof Least Resistance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":335290,"text":"At every turn, we're connecting\nthe iOS of the brain with our brain"},{"time":339445,"text":"on, for the first time, our brain's terms."},{"time":341855,"text":"In other words, we're trying to create\na zero learning-curve computer."},{"time":346738,"text":"We're building a system\nthat you've always known how to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350097,"text":"Here are the first three\ndesign guidelines that we employ"},{"time":353014,"text":"in this brand-new form of user experience."},{"time":355369,"text":"First and foremost,\nyou are the operating system."},{"time":358787,"text":"Traditional file systems\nare complex and abstract,"},{"time":361518,"text":"and they take your brain\nextra steps to decode them."},{"time":364133,"text":"We're going against the Neural Path\nof Least Resistance."},{"time":366962,"text":"Meanwhile, in augmented reality,"},{"time":369184,"text":"you can of course place\nyour holographic TED panel over here,"},{"time":374183,"text":"and your holographic email\non the other side of the desk,"},{"time":377758,"text":"and your spatial memory evolved just fine\nto go ahead and retrieve them."},{"time":383605,"text":"You could put your holographic Tesla\nthat you're shopping for --"},{"time":386657,"text":"or whatever model my legal team\ntold me to put in right before the show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390186,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391212,"text":"Perfect. And your brain knows\nexactly how to get it back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393968,"text":"The second interface guideline\nwe call \"touch to see.\""},{"time":397970,"text":"What do babies do when they see\nsomething that grabs their interest?"},{"time":402712,"text":"They try and reach out and touch it."},{"time":404452,"text":"And that's exactly how the natural\nmachine should work as well."},{"time":408439,"text":"Turns out the visual system\ngets a fundamental boost"},{"time":410951,"text":"from a sense we call proprioception --"},{"time":413384,"text":"that's the sense\nof our body parts in space."},{"time":415653,"text":"So by touching our work directly,\nwe're not only going to control it better,"},{"time":419487,"text":"we're also going to understand\nit much more deeply."},{"time":422637,"text":"Hence, touch to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424323,"text":"But it's not enough\nto experience things ourselves."},{"time":426742,"text":"We're inherently these social primates."},{"time":428993,"text":"And this leads me to our third guideline,"},{"time":431129,"text":"the holographic campfire\nfrom our first story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434537,"text":"Our mirror-neuron subsystem suggests"},{"time":436475,"text":"that we can connect with each other\nand with our work much better"},{"time":440047,"text":"if we can see each other's\nfaces and hands in 3D."},{"time":443056,"text":"So if you look at the video behind me,"},{"time":444917,"text":"you can see two Meta users\nplaying around with the same hologram,"},{"time":449250,"text":"making eye contact,\nconnected around this thing,"},{"time":451989,"text":"instead of being distracted\nby external devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456711,"text":"Let's go ahead and try this again\nwith neuroscience in mind."},{"time":464127,"text":"So again, our favorite interface,\nthe iOS of the mind."},{"time":468315,"text":"I'm going to now take a step further"},{"time":470250,"text":"and go ahead and grab this pair of glasses"},{"time":473024,"text":"and leave it right here by the desk."},{"time":474768,"text":"I'm now with you, I'm in the moment,"},{"time":476514,"text":"we're connecting."},{"time":477690,"text":"My spatial memory kicks in,\nand I can go ahead and grab it"},{"time":480632,"text":"and bring it right back here, reminding me"},{"time":482757,"text":"that I am the operating system."},{"time":484667,"text":"And now my proprioception is working,"},{"time":487071,"text":"and I can go ahead and explode\nthese glasses into a thousand parts"},{"time":490891,"text":"and touch the very sensor\nthat is currently scanning my hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495305,"text":"But it's not enough to see things alone,"},{"time":497290,"text":"so in a second, my co-founder Ray\nis going to make a 3D call --"},{"time":500286,"text":"Ray?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501468,"text":"(Ringing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503387,"text":"Hey Ray, how's it going?"},{"time":504907,"text":"Guys, I can see this guy\nin front me in full 3D."},{"time":508359,"text":"And he is photo-realistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513176,"text":"My mirror-neuron subsystem suggests\nthat this is going to replace phones"},{"time":517181,"text":"in not too long."},{"time":518601,"text":"Ray, how's it going?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520443,"text":"Ray: Great. We're live today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522832,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524405,"text":"MG: Ray, give the crowd a gift"},{"time":526541,"text":"of the holographic brain\nwe saw from the video earlier."},{"time":529200,"text":"Guys, this is not only\ngoing to change phones,"},{"time":531382,"text":"it's also going to change\nthe way we collaborate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534700,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535987,"text":"Thanks, Ray."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537169,"text":"Ray: You're welcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538344,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":539375,"text":"MG: So folks, this is the message\nthat I discovered in that bar in 2011:"},{"time":544347,"text":"The future of computers is not\nlocked inside one of these screens."},{"time":548944,"text":"It's right here, inside of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553876,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557923,"text":"So if there's one idea that I could\nleave you with here today,"},{"time":560860,"text":"it's that the natural machine\nis not some figment of the future,"},{"time":563940,"text":"it's right here in 2016."},{"time":566447,"text":"Which is why all hundred of us at Meta,"},{"time":569246,"text":"including the administrative staff,"},{"time":570945,"text":"the executives,"},{"time":572411,"text":"the designers, the engineers --"},{"time":574158,"text":"before TED2017,"},{"time":576084,"text":"we're all going to be throwing\naway our external monitors"},{"time":579765,"text":"and replacing them with a truly\nand profoundly more natural machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584909,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586124,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":590079,"text":"Thank you, appreciate it."},{"time":593501,"text":"Thanks, guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597928,"text":"Chris Anderson: So help\nme out on one thing,"},{"time":600796,"text":"because there've been a few\naugmented reality demos"},{"time":603448,"text":"shown over the last year or so out there."},{"time":606178,"text":"And there's sometimes\na debate among technologists"},{"time":608611,"text":"about, are we really seeing\nthe real thing on-screen?"},{"time":612340,"text":"There's this issue of field of view,"},{"time":614104,"text":"that somehow the technology\nis showing a broader view"},{"time":617594,"text":"than you would actually see\nwearing the glasses."},{"time":621086,"text":"Were we seeing the real deal there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622833,"text":"MG: Absolutely the real deal."},{"time":624270,"text":"Not only that,"},{"time":625451,"text":"we took extra measures to shoot it\nwith a GoPro through the actual lens"},{"time":628812,"text":"in the various videos\nthat you've seen here."},{"time":630889,"text":"We want to try to simulate\nthe experience for the world"},{"time":633489,"text":"that we're actually seeing\nthrough the glasses,"},{"time":635706,"text":"and not cut any corners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636881,"text":"CA: Thank you so much for showing us that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638929,"text":"MG: Thanks so much, I appreciate that."}]}]}